 <text id="A4044T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Hotchkiss sends a brief note to his wife, informing her of preparations for another
    battle.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">
   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <name type="recipient">Sara A. Hotchkiss</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1863-07-11">Sat. Morn July 11<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1863</date>
     </dateline>
     <salute>My <abbr expan="Dear">Dr</abbr> Wife</salute>
    </opener>

    <p>I have only time before we ride to place our troops for another sanguinary battle on the
     banks up the Antietam God grand we may be successful -- I am well -- very well, we are all
     hopeful &amp; in good spirits, never better -- Gen Lee has issued a soul stirring address
     this morning -- and our men will perform deeds of valor -- My bundle I heard from Dr. McGuire's
     in Winchester -- you may send by Frother's stage after it -- I shall do all I can to get it
     home Good bye &amp; God bless you all We hope for good &amp; feel it will come -- write
     soon </p>

    <closer>
     <salute>Your <abbr expan="Affectionate">Aff</abbr> husband</salute>
     <signed>Jed. Hotchkiss</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
